  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense. It involves making illegally-obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or other criminal enterprises) appear to come from a legitimate source. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement (introducing illegal money into the financial system)\n2. Layering (concealing the source of the money through complex transactions)\n3. Integration (making the money appear legal)\n\nIt's illegal in most countries and can result in:\n- Significant prison sentences\n- Large financial penalties\n- Seizure of assets\n- Additional criminal charges\n\nIf you're concerned about financial activities, it's best to consult with a legal professional.",
